The article discusses the recent shooting at Michigan State University where three students were killed and five students are in critical condition. The author expresses condolences for the victims and their families, as well as the communities affected by gun violence. The author mentions speaking to Governor Whitmer and deploying federal law enforcement to assist with the response efforts. The article also highlights the need for further action to address gun violence, including background checks, banning assault weapons, closing loopholes, safe storage, and eliminating immunity for gun manufacturers. The timing of the shooting, just before the five-year anniversary of the Parkland shooting, is noted as a call for Congress to take action.